history.content: CS 186 is project heavy but the exams are fine, except tough final(especially Fall 19). Next, 189 is one of the hardest CS courses in Berkeley. The minimum prep would be STAT 140+MATH 110/MATH 54/EE16A&EE16B + MATH 53. I would personally add Data100 just to be comfortable with the terms during initial weeks. If you want to be super prepared, consider doing EECS 127 + EECS 126(harder than 140) + MATH 53. People often say, CS70+Math53+Math54 is enough but I feel someone new to machine learning would be caught by surprise. So more prep is better. Next, 186 is a good class and pretty nice to have it on your resume. I can't comment on the third question. But the usual combo is CS 170 + CS 61C(letter) in a single semester.

children.subject: I took 186 last semester and it was great! The class is well organized. I have found the midterms and final to be straightforward but not easy forsho. It’s project heavy and teaches you how to work with a relatively large code base.
